did.unittitle: Army Specialized Training Division, Yale University, records

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of correspondence, transcripts, photographs, instructional materials, and administrative files documenting the Army Specialized Training Division at Yale, particularly the Army Specialized Training Program (ASTP) and the Civil Affairs Specialists Training School.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 42-A (YRG 42-A), Records of military training programs at Yale.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are partially restricted. See inventory for details.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Army Specialized Training Division, Yale University, Records (RU 89). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged by accession.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Army Training Schools, comprising the Civil Affairs Specialists Training School, the Military Intelligence Service Language School, and the Army Specialized Training Program, were established at Yale in 1943. The curricula was prescribed by the Army but administered by Yale.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of correspondence, transcripts, photographs, instructional materials, and administrative files documenting the Army Specialized Training Division at Yale, particularly the Army Specialized Training Program (ASTP) and the Civil Affairs Specialists Training School.
